description: When Mort gets challenged by the "cool kid" in school to race his dad's car, Mort crashes the car into a train and dies. He then meets Teen Death, the Grim Reaper's son, and mayhem ensues.

description: Dagger has been corrupted by Night's darkness. She is facing off against Jean Grey, Iceman and Beast of X-Factor while Night watches. Meanwhile, Cloak is trapped in the basement of the Plotnick Family of Fernwood, Ohio. Cloak is eventually released. He is able to free Dagger of the corruption. However, this comes with strings attached.
name: Blind Salvation!

volume.name: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger

description: Dagger has been blinded. At the hospital, her father and uncle receive word that her condition is permanent. Cloak returns to Holy Ghost Church where he is confronted by Det. Nales. As they talk, Cloak is used a dimensional gateway by Gromitz. Cloak is eventually kidnapped by unknown aliens with intentions to destroy the Earth.
name: Straying from the path!

volume.name: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger

description: Dagger is at home attempting to deal with the loss of her sight. Cloak has been abducted by aliens. However, he meets a man who claims to have been the previous owner of his Cloak of Darkness.
name: Alienation

volume.name: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger

description: Cloak and Dagger are attacked by demons left after Inferno. The demons intend to use Cloak and Dagger in a spell. However, Warlock, Dani Moonstar, Boom Boom, Sunspot and Gosamyr of the New Mutants are tracking the demons.
name: Isolation!

volume.name: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger

description: Cloak has apparently died. Dagger is making strides in dealing with the loss of sight. Mayhem visits her former partner Det. Nales. However, Cloak's Darkforce powers have transitioned to Ecstasy.
name: Cloak is No More!

volume.name: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger

description: Ecstasy, the current wielder of the Darkforce, makes arrangements to go to New York. Tandy is learning to deal with day to day normal life as a blind person. However, she nearly becomes the victim of a traffic accident. She is rescued by a most unlikely savior.
name: Agony is Ecstasy

description: The Acts of Vengeance crossover event continues. The Avengers team up with Cloak and Dagger against Hulk and Hydroman, plus the X-Men villains Fenris and Rock. All in this Giant-Sized adventure!
name: To Battle the Avengers

volume.name: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger

description: Cloak and Dagger visit the former Father Francis Delgado in the hospital. Brigid O'Reilly is staying with Det. Nales. However, O'Reilly has a secret. At the hospital, Cloak and Dagger encounter a group of Soldiers.
name: The uncontrollable...X-Force!

volume.name: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger

description: While Cloak must save Brigid and Rusty, Dagger fights alone against the Marked Man.

description: Cloak and Dagger's battle against Dr. Doom continues, but things go from bad to worse when Mr. Jip joins the fray. How can our young heroes hope to defeat both villains at once? Beats us!
name: The Big Oblivion Scenario

volume.name: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger

description: The mutant virus Mutatis is loose in the near future, and it's turning people into monstrous creatures. One infected man is offered an antidote, bu the price is he must find other infected people and kill them.

Infected with the deadly Mutatis virus, ex-cop Lyle Crane joins forces with a fellow peace officer to stop the spread of the virus by killing three other infected people. The discovery of a fourth victim may make the murders a useless exercise and may also destroy the future-world.

Conclusion! Infected ex-cop, Lyle Crane, has finally disposed of all the other suspected carriers of the virus Mutatis. Having saved Hydropolis from extinction, Crane expects the antidote from the man who hired him. Unfortunately, Crane discovers that there is one more carrier--the president of Hydropolis!
